snippet.textDisplay: So you probably won't see this but if you do this is for your eyelids being dry. Vitamin E capsules, you poke them with a needle of any sort and squeeze the oil onto your fingertip and apply it onto your eyelids. snippet.textDisplay: Hi Jeffree, I have had extremely dry eyelids for years now and still haven’t found a perfect solution. (By extremely bad I mean like flakey dead skin all over my upper eyelid and under eye) I’ve been using a daily eczema cream, a moisturizing under eye cream, and have recently tried a humidifier in my room when I sleep. The humidifier has really helped in my room at night since it’s so dry and I’m there for like half of my day/night. Hope this helps anyone struggling with something similar to me, dry flakey eyelids is terrible for a makeup lover and it SUCKS!
